{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3e226dcc-ab1f-4eac-83b6-615d1dcf8e9d","content":"\n\nTo register your MCP server in the official **MCP Registry** (hosted at [github.com/modelcontextprotocol/servers](https://github.com/modelcontextprotocol/servers)):\n\n1. **Fork** the `modelcontextprotocol/servers` repo on GitHub.\n2. **Add your server** to the community servers list by editing the repository's registry/catalog (typically `README.md` or a JSON registry file — check their current contribution guide).\n3. **Open a Pull Request** with:\n   - Server name & description\n   - NuGet package link\n   - Transport type (e.g., `stdio`)\n   - Installation/usage instructions\n4. Wait for maintainers to **review & merge**.\n\n**Quick links:**\n- Registry repo: `https://github.com/modelcontextprotocol/servers`\n- Contributing guide: check `CONTRIBUTING.md` in that repo for the latest submission format\n\n> **Tip:** The registry format changes occasionally. Before submitting, read their current `CONTRIBUTING.md` to ensure your PR matches the expected schema/format. Some registries now use a structured JSON or YAML file rather than a README table.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"48cd2a42-0df7-4744-b77a-d63f91342f47","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to register their C# MCP server in the official MCP Registry. This is a general knowledge question about the MCP (Model Context Protocol) ecosystem. Let me provide what I know and also check for any relevant information online.","outputTokens":339},"id":"133c5d44-fe26-475a-b727-0a31ce551a40","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:58:37.491Z","parentId":"160e08f7-7180-41a3-b55d-f6ff5d714a23"}
